[5, 5, "Jami` at-Tirmidhi", "Jami` at-Tirmidhi is a collection of hadith compiled by Imam Abu `Isa Muhammad at-Tirmidhi (rahimahullah). His collection is unanimously considered to be one of the six canonical collections of hadith (Kutub as-Sittah) of the Sunnah of the Prophet (ï·º). It contains roughly 4400 hadith (with repetitions) in 46 books.", null, "The numbering below corresponds with the numbering scheme started by Shaykh Ahmad Shakir, then continued by Shaykh Muhammad Fu'ad 'Abdul Baaqi, and finished by Shaykh Ibrahim 'Atwah 'Aood (rahimahumullah).", "en"]
